OL,5, An Italian man has admitted stealing   
OL,6, more than 1,000 unpublished            
OL,7, manuscripts, many written by           
OL,8, high-profile authors.                  
OL,10,FFilippo Bernardini impersonated figures
OL,11,Ffrom the publishing industry to trick  
OL,12,Fpeople into handing over their works.  
OL,14,FHe used his inside industry knowledge, 
OL,15,Fhaving been employed by the publishing 
OL,16,Fgiant Simon & Schuster in London.      
OL,18,FBernardini, 30, pleaded guilty in New  
OL,19,FYork to wire fraud, but his motive has 
OL,20,Fnever been clear.                      
